.TH "__vmbus_recvpacket" 9 "__vmbus_recvpacket" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__vmbus_recvpacket \- Retrieve the user packet on the specified channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __vmbus_recvpacket
.BI "(struct vmbus_channel *channel "  ","
.BI "void *buffer "  ","
.BI "u32 bufferlen "  ","
.BI "u32 *buffer_actual_len "  ","
.BI "u64 *requestid "  ","
.BI "bool raw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "channel" 12
Pointer to vmbus_channel structure
.IP "buffer" 12
Pointer to the buffer you want to receive the data into.
.IP "bufferlen" 12
Maximum size of what the buffer can hold.
.IP "buffer_actual_len" 12
The actual size of the data after it was received.
.IP "requestid" 12
Identifier of the request
.IP "raw" 12
true means keep the vmpacket_descriptor header in the received data.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Receives directly from the hyper-v vmbus and puts the data it received
into Buffer. This will receive the data unparsed from hyper-v.

Mainly used by Hyper-V drivers.
